   <div id="div-comment-2456" class="thechild">
      <div class="leftarea cleft">
         	  </div>
      <div class="rightarea cright">      
      <div class="comment-author vcard by">
         <cite class="fn">lol</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>      </div>
      
      <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://reviewsindepth.com/2012/09/would-you-take-the-honeymoon-pill/comment-page-1/#comment-2456">September 22, 2012 at 1:35 pm</a></div>

      <p>tl; dr</p>

      <div class="reply">
         <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/09/would-you-take-the-honeymoon-pill/?replytocom=2456#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-2456", "2456", "respond", "2892")'>Reply</a>      </div>
    </div>
      </div>
   </li>               
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
   <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-2467">
   <div id="div-comment-2467" class="thechild">
      <div class="leftarea cleft">
         	  </div>
      <div class="rightarea cright">      
      <div class="comment-author vcard by">
         <cite class="fn">forrest</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>      </div>
      
      <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://reviewsindepth.com/2012/09/would-you-take-the-honeymoon-pill/comment-page-1/#comment-2467">September 23, 2012 at 9:35 pm</a></div>

      <p>Thanks for all that effort.  It was a long read, but in an area I am very interested in.  Interesting thought experiment and a great exercise for anyone who has been involved in the odd setup that is human mating.  Why do we choose whom we choose and why do they choose us?  What common features characterize the evolution of pair relationships and what is the common period and sequence of each?   It is desirable to short circuit biology if these behaviors/attitudes have a survival advantage?  It dissolution desirable?  (It SEEMS that it would encourage genetic diversity.)  For a male, is a sound strategy consistently and deceptively telegraphing commitment while withholding it?  Is commitment the poison of passion?  How can one game the system that is one&#8217;s self in the interest of improving a relationship (i.e., scheduled and significant duration absence, etc.)  Again, good read.  I have new fodder for thought and thank you for the effort.</p>

      <div class="reply">
         <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/09/would-you-take-the-honeymoon-pill/?replytocom=2467#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-2467", "2467", "respond", "2892")'>Reply</a>      </div>
    </div>
      </div>
   </li>               
<ul class="children">
   <li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2482">
   <div id="div-comment-2482" class="thechild">
